	(58,1,'2014-05-19 15:42:54','2014-05-19 15:42:54','<p style=\"color: #000000;\">At DSS Services we provide our customers with good knowledge when it comes to selling a house. First you need to find a real estate agent to trust. Then you can make plans to start seeing homes at your price range. There are things to look at before you decided to purchase a home like for example, if it’s been remodel recently or have new appliances. Another thing is you have to evaluate your situation, like if you would like to stay in your neighborhood or if you need more space.</p>\r\nNext step plan your selling strategy after you crunch the numbers and decided that it’s the right time to sell, come up with a plan to achieve the financial and personal goals. Then to close the deal, review every offer carefully, evaluate the buyer and negotiate terms so you can come to a deal. The physical condition, overall structural, integrity of the home, including roof, foundation, electrical system, etc can help in making the choice.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #000000;\">In Conclusion, look at possible status of pending lawsuits, compliances with local building and zoning codes.</span>','Seller\'s Guide','','publish','open','open','','sellers-guide','','','2014-06-19 19:04:03','2014-06-19 19:04:03','',0,'http://localhost:8888/dssserv/?page_id=58',0,'page','',0),
